Frédéric P. Villoutreix  Consultant, Schweitzer-Mauduit International, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 0 Board Members in 0 different organizations across 1 different industries.53$3,638,926As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Frederic P. Villoutreix has been Consultant of Schweitzer-Mauduit International, Inc. since May 5, 2017. Mr. Villoutreix served as an Executive Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Schweitzer-Mauduit International, Inc. since January 1, 2009 until May 5, 2017. Mr. Villoutreix served as the Chief Operating Officer of Schweitzer-mauduit International, Inc. from February 1, 2006 to December 2008 and its Interim President of French Operations from December 7, 2006 ... to June 1, 2007. Mr. Villoutreix joined Schweitzer-Mauduit from Compagnie de Saint- Gobain, where he worked since 1990. He held key manufacturing positions in Europe and the United States with Saint-Gobain, including General Manager, World Construction Products and Stone, Luxemburg from 2001 to 2004 and served as Vice President, Abrasives Europe and Coated Abrasives World from 2004 to 2005 with 33 operating locations. He served as an Executive Director of Schweitzer-Mauduit International, Inc. since June 1, 2007 until May 5, 2017. Mr. Villoutreix holds an Master's degree in Science and Engineering, with a major in Economics from Ecole Polytechnique, Palaiseau, France and PhD in Engineering and Management from Ecole des Mines, Paris, France.Read Full Background




